%N A397412 Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(s) * Product_{p prime} (1 - 1/p^s + 1/p^(2*s-1)).
%C A397412 If we choose the equivalent DGF zeta(k*s-k+1) * fk(s), then fk(1) will always be = 1, but fk'(1) = fk(1) * Sum_{p prime} ((k-2)*p + 1) * log(p) / (p*(p-1)) is convergent only for k=2.
%C A397412 Sum_{k=1..10^m} a(k) for m = 1..15 is 8, 54, 529, 5087, 50458, 501061, 5013706, 50060105, 500022805, 5000592487, 50007199931, 500015598796, 5000037108939, 50000455685720, 500001734289997. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2026
%H A397412 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A397412/b397412.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397412 Vaclav Kotesovec, <a href="/A397412/a397412_1.jpg">Plot of Sum_{k=1..n} a(k)/n for n = 1..500000000</a>
%F A397412 Multiplicative with a(p) = 0, and a(p^e) = p for e >= 2. - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2026
%F A397412 Let f(s) = Product_{p prime} (1 + p^(2-3*s) - p^(1-2*s) - p^s) / (1-p^s).
%F A397412 Dirichlet g.f.: zeta(2*s-1) * f(s).
%F A397412 f(1) = 1.
%F A397412 f'(1) = f(1) * Sum_{p prime} log(p) / (p*(p-1)) = A138312.
%F A397412 Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ n/2. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_ and _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2026
%t A397412 f[p_, 1] := 0; f[p_, e_] := p; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 22 2026 *)
%o A397412 (PARI) for(n=1, 100, print1(direuler(p=2, n, 1/(1-X)*(1 - X + p*X^2))[n], ", "))
